---
description: Testing conventions
alwaysApply: true
---

# Style

- Use pytest with plain functions (no classes).
- Name tests: `test_<what>_<expected>`.

# Scope

- Prefer unit tests for services.
- Keep API tests minimal.

# Mocking

- Mock all external deps: LLM, APIs, DB.
- No real network calls.

# Database

- Do not use real DB.
- Prefer mocked repositories.
- Optional: in-memory SQLite.

# LLM

- Mock responses (deterministic).
- Test parsing + error handling.

# Rules

- Tests must be fast and deterministic.
- No randomness without fixed seed.
